# UI Components Guide

This project uses Shadcn UI components built on top of Radix UI primitives, with Tailwind CSS for styling.

## Component Library
The project uses the following UI component libraries:
- Radix UI primitives for accessible components
- Shadcn UI for styled components
- Lucide React for icons
- Tailwind CSS for styling

## Key UI Components
- [language-toggle.tsx](mdc:components/language-toggle.tsx): Language switching component
- [logo.tsx](mdc:components/logo.tsx): Application logo component
- [theme-provider.tsx](mdc:components/theme-provider.tsx): Dark/light theme provider

## Styling
- Global styles are defined in [globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)
- Tailwind configuration in [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts)
- Uses `class-variance-authority` for component variants
- Implements dark mode through `next-themes`

## Available Radix UI Components
The project includes the following Radix UI components:
- Accordion
- Alert Dialog
- Avatar
- Checkbox
- Dialog
- Dropdown Menu
- Navigation Menu
- Popover
- Select
- Tabs
- Toast
- Tooltip
- And more...

## Usage Guidelines
1. Use Shadcn UI components from the `components/ui` directory
2. Follow the established styling patterns using Tailwind CSS
3. Implement dark mode support using the theme provider
4. Ensure all components are accessible using Radix UI primitives
